<TEXT>
   The dollar firmed in quiet trading yesterday as dealers awaited the release of <LOCATION>U.S.</LOCATION> economic indicators and reflected on swings earlier in the week. 

   "After <DATE>Monday</DATE> and <DATE>Tuesday</DATE>, we needed a day of rest," said <PERSON>Robert Hatcher</PERSON>, vice president and corporate foreign-exchange dealer at <ORGANIZATION>Barclays Bank International Ltd.</ORGANIZATION>, <LOCATION>New York</LOCATION>. 
